{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "heydon-pickering",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "One blocking fix: delete button aria-label needed",
    "content": "Task #15 a11y review: **APPROVED WITH ONE BLOCKING FIX.**\n\n**Blocking**: Delete buttons in `templates/inbox_item.html` lack item-specific accessible names. Currently just \"Delete\" -- screen reader users can't distinguish which item each button acts on. Fix is one line: add `aria-label=\"Delete: {{ item.title }}\"` to the button. Same pattern as the existing todo list delete buttons. WCAG SC 4.1.2 / SC 2.4.6.\n\n**Non-blocking note**: The too-long title error message in `inbox.rs` is computed then discarded (line 135). Template has no error display for this case. `maxlength=\"300\"` prevents it for most users, so non-blocking.\n\nEverything else is well done -- semantic markup, proper labels, HTMX announcements, focus management, no duplicate capture inputs, axe-core coverage. Once the delete button aria-label is fixed, I'm at full approval."
  }
}
